# Phase 16 — Cloudflare Change Evidence Archive

## Objective

Build an immutable, structured evidence archive for all Cloudflare CI reports, baseline diffs, release approvals, post-release verifications, and incident reviews. This archive provides the single source of truth for all change evidence within the ZeaZ Platform Cloudflare governance sequence.

This phase must NOT deploy, apply, destroy, or mutate Cloudflare. It is a documentation and template layer only.

---

## Branch Name

```
fix/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive
```

## Commit Message

```
docs(cloudflare): add change evidence archive model
```

---

## Scope

- Define the directory structure and naming convention for the evidence archive
- Create retention policy, index template, release approval template, and incident review template
- Update infra/cloudflare/README.md with Phase 16 entry
- All examples must be sanitized (no real secrets, tokens, API responses, or credentials)

---

## Non-Goals

- Do NOT run `wrangler deploy`, `terraform apply`, `tofu apply`, or any Cloudflare write
- Do NOT add live CI report data or real incident data
- Do NOT commit secrets, tokens, credentials, or private API responses
- Do NOT start or restart any services
- Do NOT edit `/etc/cloudflared/config.yml`
- Do NOT modify unrelated files

---

## Safety Rules

1. All examples in evidence templates must use placeholder/sanitized values
2. Never reference real Cloudflare API tokens, tunnel credentials, or DNS zone IDs in examples
3. Evidence archive must be clearly marked as a documentation structure — not a live store
4. All docs must clearly separate: live runtime facts | repo intent | Terraform ownership | manual actions | unresolved drift | evidence outputs
5. No exact-copy of live configuration allowed

---

