## Required Evidence Archive Structure

The archive directory must be documented (not necessarily created with real files) as follows:

```
docs/infra/evidence/cloudflare/
  README.md              ← archive overview and usage guide
  index.md               ← running index of all change records
  YYYY/
    MM/
      CHANGE-ID/
        summary.md                  ← what changed, who approved, when
        ci-report.md                ← CI gate output (sanitized)
        baseline-diff.md            ← diff against last known baseline
        scanner-output.json         ← sanitized scanner result (no secrets)
        release-approval.md         ← filled release approval template
        post-release-verification.md← verified gate results after release
        incident-review.md          ← filled if incident occurred (optional)
```

CHANGE-ID format: `CF-YYYY-MM-NNN` (e.g., `CF-2025-06-001`)

---

## Required Deliverables

### Documentation Files

1. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive.md`**
   - Archive model overview
   - Directory structure (as above)
   - CHANGE-ID naming convention
   - How to open a change record
   - How to close and archive a change record
   - Rules: sanitized examples only, no real credentials
   - Link to retention policy

2. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-retention-policy.md`**
   - Retention periods by evidence type:
     - CI reports: 90 days minimum
     - Release approvals: 1 year minimum
     - Incident reviews: 2 years minimum
     - Drift reports: 1 year minimum
     - Exception register: 1 year after closure
   - Archive ownership
   - Deletion / expiry process
   - What must never be deleted
   - What must never be stored (real secrets, credentials)

3. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-index-template.md`**
   - Template for `docs/infra/evidence/cloudflare/index.md`
   - Columns: Change ID | Date | Type | System Area | Owner | Status | Summary link
   - Example sanitized rows

4. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-release-approval-template.md`**
   - Required fields:
     - Change ID
     - Change title
     - System area
     - Owner
     - Approver
     - Date / time (UTC)
     - Risk level (from Phase 17 scoring)
     - Environment (dev / staging / prod)
     - Rollback plan reference
     - Evidence links
     - Checklist (pre-change, post-change)
     - Sign-off
   - Sanitized example

5. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-incident-review-template.md`**
   - Required fields:
     - Incident ID
     - Change ID (if triggered by a change)
     - Date / time discovered (UTC)
     - Date / time resolved (UTC)
     - Severity
     - System area affected
     - Owner
     - Root cause
     - Timeline
     - Impact assessment
     - Remediation steps taken
     - Rollback used (yes/no + evidence)
     - Lessons learned
     - Follow-up actions with owners and dates
   - Sanitized example

6. **`infra/cloudflare/README.md`** *(update)*
   - Add Phase 16 entry with links to all deliverables above

7. **`docs/infra/evidence/cloudflare/README.md`** *(create)*
   - Archive overview and usage guide
   - How to find a change record
   - Sanitized example structure

