## Suggested Commands

```bash
# Create branch
git checkout -b fix/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive

# Create archive directory (structure only — no real data)
mkdir -p docs/infra/evidence/cloudflare

# After writing files, verify
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-retention-policy.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-index-template.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-release-approval-template.md
cat docs/infra/cloudflare-incident-review-template.md

# Secret check
grep -RInE '(token|secret|password|credential|api[_-]?key)' \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-retention-policy.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-release-approval-template.md \
  docs/infra/cloudflare-incident-review-template.md || echo "No secrets found"

# Git status
git diff --name-only

# Commit
git add docs/infra/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-retention-policy.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-index-template.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-release-approval-template.md \
        docs/infra/cloudflare-incident-review-template.md \
        docs/infra/evidence/cloudflare/README.md \
        infra/cloudflare/README.md
git commit -m "docs(cloudflare): add change evidence archive model"

# Push and open PR
git push origin fix/cloudflare-change-evidence-archive
gh pr create --title "docs(cloudflare): add change evidence archive model" \
  --body "Phase 16: Adds immutable evidence archive model, retention policy, release approval template, incident review template, and index. Read-only governance layer. No deploy. No secrets."
```

---

## Final Response Format for AI Agent

When this phase is complete, report:

1. Files created (list with paths)
2. Files updated (list with paths)
3. Short summary of each doc (1–2 lines)
4. Validation commands run and their output summary
5. Any warnings (sanitization issues, missing fields)
6. Git status summary (`git diff --stat`)
7. Suggested commit command (already done or ready to run)

**Do not claim that anything was deployed.**
**Do not claim that Cloudflare was changed.**
**Do not claim that Terraform was applied.**
**Do not store any real incident data, credentials, or live configuration in the archive.**
